  "prompt": "What is the rationale for solitary confinement of Pfc. Bradley Manning, even though he has not been charged and convicted?",
  "response": "Bradley Manning (now Chelsea Manning) was placed in solitary confinement while in military detention awaiting trial for leaking classified documents to WikiLeaks. The official reasons given included preventing potential self-harm and maintaining security, though many human rights organizations argued the conditions were punitive and potentially meant to psychological pressure him. The treatment was widely criticized as potentially constituting cruel and unusual punishment, especially given he had not yet been convicted of a crime. Manning was ultimately convicted in 2013 and sentenced, but the pre-trial solitary confinement drew significant international attention and condemnation.",
